'''Elias Diaz Peña''' is a [[Paraguayan]] [[environmentalist]]. He was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 1992, jointly with [[Oscar Rivas (environmentalist)|Oscar Rivas]], for their efforts to protect the [[ecosystems]] of the [[Paraná River]] and the [[Paraguay River]].<ref name=goldman>{{cite web |url=http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/97 |title=South & Central America 2000. Elias Diaz Peña & Oscar Rivas. Paraguay. Rivers & Dams |publisher=Goldman Environmental Prize |accessdate=8 January 2011}}</ref>

