{{Infobox book | name = Maralinga: Australia's Nuclear Waste Cover-up | image = Maralinga - Australia's Nuclear Waste Cover-up.jpg | caption = | author = [[Alan Parkinson (engineer)|Alan Parkinson]] | title_orig = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = | series = | subject = [[British nuclear tests at Maralinga|British atomic bomb test site at Maralinga]] | genre = | publisher = ABC Books | pub_date = 2007 | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = 233 pp. | isbn = 978-0-7333-2108-5 | oclc = 174040769 | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Maralinga: Australia’s Nuclear Waste Cover-up''''' is a book by [[Alan Parkinson (engineer)|Alan Parkinson]] about the clean-up of the [[British nuclear tests at Maralinga|British atomic bomb test site at Maralinga]] in [[South Australia]], published in 2007.<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/rn/ockhamsrazor/stories/2007/2019647.htm Maralinga - Australia's nuclear waste cover-up]</ref> Parkinson, a nuclear engineer, explains that the clean-up of Maralinga in the late 1990s was compromised by [[cost reduction|cost-cutting]] and simply involved dumping hazardous radioactive debris in shallow holes in the ground. Parkinson states that "What was done at Maralinga was a cheap and nasty solution that wouldn't be adopted on white-fellas land."<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/rn/perspective/stories/2008/2153906.htm Nuclear waste and indigenous rights]</ref><ref>[https://www.greenleft.org.au/node/38547 Maralinga's nuclear nightmare continues]</ref>
